16/01/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The organised crime prosecution announced on Friday (January 14th) they have arrested two Romanians suspected of belonging to a drug cartel that planned to transport 90m euros worth of cocaine to Western Europe. 
The two men, Constantin Nadolu and Catalin Iosef, are charged with being members of a Colombian organised crime group. 
(AP, Romania Libera, Ziare, Adevarul - 14/01/11)
